      • getLikeCount

        public int getLikeCount()
                 throws ParsingException
        Description copied from interface: CommentsInfoItemExtractor
        Return the like count of the comment, or -1 if it's unavailable
        NOTE: Currently only implemented for YT getLikeCount() with limitations (only approximate like count is returned)
        Specified by:
        getLikeCount in interface CommentsInfoItemExtractor
        Throws:
        ParsingException
        See Also:
        StreamExtractor.getLikeCount()
        Implementation Note:
        The method is parsing internally a localized string.
        • More than 1k likes will result in an inaccurate number
        • This will fail for other languages than English. However as long as the Extractor only uses "en-GB" (as seen in YoutubeService.SUPPORTED_LANGUAGES) everything will work fine.

        Consider using getTextualLikeCount()
